+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XCyVwEXQTg1WBJZLZ3XREe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Starting autopilot. I'll narrate each decision. Proceeding through key design questions:\n\n**Q1: Overall architecture pattern?**\n→ Choosing: Single `TaskQueue` manager class with internal `Queue` instances per named queue\nReasoning: A central manager provides a clean API surface, handles cross-queue concerns (task dependencies, shutdown), while per-queue instances encapsulate queue-specific state (priority ordering, concurrency, middleware).\n\n**Q2: Task ID generation?**\n→ Choosing: `crypto.randomUUID()` (built-in Node.js)\nReasoning: No external dependencies needed, produces standard UUIDs, available in Node 16+.\n\n**Q3: Priority queue data structure?**\n→ Choosing: Sorted insertion into an array with binary search\nReasoning: Simple, no dependencies. For an in-memory system this is performant enough. A proper heap would be overkill for this use case.\n\n**Q4: Task state machine?**\n→ Choosing: States: `pending` → `processing` → `completed`/`failed`/`cancelled`, plus `blocked` (for dependencies) and `delayed` (for scheduled tasks)\nReasoning: Clear lifecycle, each state transition is well-defined.\n\n**Q5: Event system for progress/subscriptions?**\n→ Choosing: Simple EventEmitter pattern (Node.js built-in)\nReasoning: Already available, no dependencies, fits the subscription model perfectly.\n\n**Q6: Cron parsing approach?**\n→ Choosing: Hand-written parser for the simple subset required\nReasoning: Only need `*/N * * * *`, `0 * * * *`, `0 0 * * *` — trivial to parse without a library.\n\n**Q7: Middleware pattern?**\n→ Choosing: Koa-style `(task, next) => ...` chain\nReasoning: Matches the spec exactly, well-understood pattern.\n\n**Q8: File organization?**\n→ Choosing: Single-file core with types, split into logical sections\nReasoning: With 12 phases of tightly coupled features, splitting into many files creates unnecessary import complexity. A well-organized single module with clear sections is more maintainable for this scope.\n\nNow let me write the design document and proceed directly to implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":163,"cache_read_input_tokens":26462,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":163},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0490614c-768c-4866-acee-66d51e083bfa","uuid":"0c4f023b-80b3-4104-84b4-0b7b8bf25b99"}
+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XCyVwEXQTg1WBJZLZ3XREe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01M92qJ1yB8cqUvuqDAKZwoJ","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-task-queue-design.md","content":"# Task Queue System Design\n\n## Architecture\n\nSingle `TaskQueue` class as the main entry point, managing multiple named `Queue` instances internally. Each queue maintains its own priority-ordered task list, concurrency tracking, middleware stack, and dead letter queue.\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Single manager class** (`TaskQueue`) with per-queue state isolation\n2. **Task IDs**: `crypto.randomUUID()`\n3. **Priority ordering**: Sorted array with insertion sort (priority 1-10, FIFO within same priority)\n4. **Task states**: `pending`, `processing`, `completed`, `failed`, `cancelled`, `blocked`, `delayed`\n5. **Events**: Node.js `EventEmitter` for progress subscriptions\n6. **Cron**: Hand-written parser for the required subset\n7. **Middleware**: `(task, next) => void` chain pattern\n8. **File structure**: `src/index.ts` as main export, core implementation in `src/task-queue.ts`\n\n## Data Model\n\n```\nTask {\n  id: string (UUID)\n  payload: unknown\n  status: TaskStatus\n  priority: number (1-10, default 5)\n  queueName: string\n  createdAt: Date\n  availableAt: Date | null\n  attempts: number\n  maxRetries: number\n  backoffMs: number\n  lastError: string | null\n  progress: number (0-100)\n  progressMessage: string | null\n  dependencies: string[]\n}\n```\n\n## Implementation Phases\n\nAll 12 phases implemented incrementally in `src/task-queue.ts`, exported from `src/index.ts`.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":163,"cache_read_input_tokens":26462,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":163},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"stand